results.name: Permutation of natural numbers induced by Catalan Automorphism *A074684 acting on the parenthesizations encoded by A014486/A063171.
comment: This bijection maps between the "standard" ordering of binary trees as encoded by A014486 and "variant A quaternary encoding" as explained in the sequence A085184.
This is a rare example of a simply defined Catalan Automorphism where the cycle count sequence (A089411) is not monotone. (See A127296 for a much more complex example.)
link: Index entries for sequences that are permutations of the natural numbers
program: (Scheme function implementing this automorphism on list-structures/S-expressions:)
xref: The number of cycles, maximum cycle sizes and LCM's of all cycle sizes in subpermutations limited by A014137 and A014138 are given by A089411, A086586 and A089412.
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Sep 11 2002
